text: Mathilda Lindholm (born 17 July 1995) is a Finnish badminton player, specializing in doubles play. She started playing badminton at 5 years old, then in 2005, she joined Finnish national badminton team. In 2011, she won gold medal at the European U17 Badminton Championships in mixed doubles event with Iikka Heino. She also finished as runner-up in senior level at the 2010 Finnish Open and 2015 Hellas International in women's doubles event with Jenny Nyström.
